		<pubDate>Sat, 01 Jan 2011 15:27:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>admin</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Pastor's Blog]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://calvarymontclair.org/?p=1420</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Church family and friends, I&#8217;m lovin&#8217; the prospect of a new beginning! 2010 was a difficult year for me personally, for Calvary Chapel, and I know it was for some of you also. But oh boy! It&#8217;s over! Thank the Lord we all made it! The year was not without blessings however. There was an [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><strong>Church family and friends,</strong></p>
<p>I&#8217;m lovin&#8217; the prospect of a new beginning! 2010 was a difficult year for me personally, for Calvary Chapel, and I know it was for some of you also. But oh boy! It&#8217;s over! Thank the Lord we all made it!</p>
<p>The year was not without blessings however. There was an unexpected but very positive change in our church board, our Wednesday night study took off &#8211; often surpassing Sunday morning in attendance and ministry. The biggest blessing by far was seeing the radio station permit come to fruition at the very end &#8211; an asset that will be a real game-changer in 2011.</p>
<p>As our Lord has granted us new life (Romans 6:4, 2 Corinthians 5:17), as His mercies are new every morning (Lamentations 3:22-23), as He has a plan for the future for us (Jeremiah 29:11), may we be of Paul&#8217;s mind when he said &#8220;&#8230;one thing I do, forgetting those things which are behind and reaching forward to those things which are ahead, I press toward the goal for the prize of the upward call of God in Christ Jesus.&#8221; (Philippians 3:13-14).</p>
<p>Many blessings in this new season! May His mighty hand be upon us all in 2011!</p>
<p>Pastor George</p>
